Instruction to run:
	1. From the directory where file-explorer.js is kept use the following command to run the application
	    node file-explorer.js <dir1> <dir2> <dir3> ...

	    example : node file-explorer.js ~/Documents ~/Downloads ./Test 

	2. Open the following url in any browser to see the application in action
	    http://localhost:8888/

	3. Once the file explorer is opened in browser you can expand or collapse any directory similar to any file explorer

	4. To view changes made to files in the specified directory (additions, deletions, renames etc) you can simply collapse its parent and expand 